  "html": "<h1>Applies to</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>PHP</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  <h1>What to Check For</h1>\r\n  <p>Verify that domain and path values of session cookies are strict.</p>\r\n  <h1>Why</h1>\r\n  <p>Setting strict domain and path values on session cookies makes it harder for attackers to hijack user sessions.</p>\r\n  <h1>How to Check</h1>\r\n  <p>To verify that domain and path values of session cookies are strict:</p>\r\n  <ol>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <p>\r\n        <strong>Define a strict cookie path.</strong> Use the application path as the cookie path.</p>\r\n      <li>\r\n        <p>\r\n          <strong>Define a strict cookie domain.</strong> If the application uses a subdomain, use it as the cookie domain value.</p>\r\n        <li>\r\n          <p>\r\n            <strong>Examine the path and domain values.</strong> View the <em>php.ini</em> file to make sure that strict values for the session cookie domain and path properties are set using \"<em>session.cookie_domain</em>\" and \"<em>session.cookie_path</em>\" directives respectively.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n      </li>\r\n    </li>\r\n  </ol>\r\n  <h1>How to Fix</h1>\r\n  <p>To set strict domain and path values on session cookies:</p>\r\n  <ol>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <p>\r\n        <strong>Define a strict cookie path.</strong> Use the application path as the cookie path.</p>\r\n      <li>\r\n        <p>\r\n          <strong>Define a strict cookie domain.</strong> If the application uses a subdomain, use it as the cookie domain value.</p>\r\n        <li>\r\n          <p>\r\n            <strong>Set the path and domain values. </strong>Edit the <em>php.ini</em> file. Set \"<em>session.cookie_path</em>\" to the strict cookie path. Set \"<em>session.cookie_domain</em>\" to the strict cookie domain.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n      </li>\r\n    </li>\r\n  </ol>\r\n  <h1>Additional Resources</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>For more information about PHP runtime configuration, please see <a href=\"http://php.net/manual/en/session.configuration.php\">http://php.net/manual/en/session.configuration.php</a></li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  <h1>Secure Session Management Guidelines</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/c940ef8d-5bca-4351-b94a-f4db44043028\">Protect Session IDs</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/b42309de-b99e-4a32-a36e-6c4cdf9e3a6e\">Use PHP Session Management</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/e00c3d06-d939-494d-a42c-88878f26f2fc\">Use Strong Session IDs</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/96aa6669-a0c8-432b-9876-dd8da36ce179\">Change Session IDs During Authentication</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/f3dacae2-77f1-44d5-96d2-1a08318e4943\">Make Inactive Sessions Time-out</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/775c2307-9cd9-4dce-a419-6fe406fb1f20\">Make Sessions Time-out</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/7d873b52-217e-43e8-8fe9-a5dcf52bf030\">Destroy Sessions When Users Log Out</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/62bb739d-e0fe-425b-9fb9-af286914ac7e\">Place Logout Links on All Pages That Require Authentication</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/4a16cea2-b475-4371-9379-f3d27d43986a\">Set the Domain and Path Values on Sessions Cookies</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/bfdf9875-69c4-43d2-978c-b9c09d8ca6c2\">Set the HTTPOnly Flag on Session Cookies</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/9fec2088-1a0c-42ba-86c0-445afbc48f62\">Set the Secure Flag on Session Cookies</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  <h1>Secure Session Management Checklists</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/23b55746-8cef-427d-b91b-18949f2538f5\">Session IDs Are Protected</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/bc3f332a-c395-486b-b095-6b7cc4935367\">PHP Session Management Is Used</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/da9827ed-e835-49a8-b6d0-7feee8cb5a09\">Strong Session IDs Are Used</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/655b5bf0-8dc9-484b-844a-b8d5f4099645\">Session IDs Are Changed During Authentication</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/6947d991-5eb6-4433-b32a-897d77d447f2\">Inactive Sessions Time-out</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/3b9db169-19a6-4e3c-bbf8-6423e77060b2\">Sessions Have an Absolute Time-out</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/8f94d6fd-ece9-40f8-8db6-2f2addb82fa3\">Sessions Are Destroyed When Users Log Out</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/197d4a9f-0a73-4fb0-913c-fc53c73c74d2\">All Pages that Use Authentication Have Logout Links</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/1d600d77-9cca-4c20-bdb1-07707f83e676\">The Domain and Path Values of Session Cookies Are Strict</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/c2b6ad74-7e7f-4b4d-8a55-8b55933b54ac\">The HTTPOnly Flag Is Set on Session Cookies</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/96928660-b73e-497c-a98e-e4856ff895e6\">The Secure Flag Is Set on Session Cookies</a>\r\n    </li>\r\n  </ul>"
